# WordPress.org SVN trunk sync

Development happens in this Git repo (`vendorhub-woocommerce`). Publishing uses a sibling SVN working copy.

| Role | Path |
|------|------|
| Dev (Git) | `D:\Dev\Torpedo Solutions Inc\vendorhub-woocommerce` |
| SVN publish | `D:\Dev\Torpedo Solutions Inc\vendorhub-for-woocommerce-svn` |
| SVN URL | `https://plugins.svn.wordpress.org/myvendorhub-for-woocommerce` |

## After changing plugin ship files

When you modify any file that ships in the plugin ZIP, sync to SVN trunk before finishing:

```powershell
.\scripts\sync-svn-trunk.ps1
```

If you changed listing images in `assets/*.png`, also sync assets:

```powershell
.\scripts\sync-svn-trunk.ps1 -SyncAssets
```

### Files that sync to `trunk/`

- `vendorhub.php`, `readme.txt`, `uninstall.php`
- `includes/`, `admin/`, `languages/`

Do **not** copy dev-only paths: `tests/`, `scripts/`, `docs/`, `.github/`, `composer.*`, `*.zip`.

### Files that sync to `assets/` (not trunk)

- `assets/*.png` only (banners, icons, screenshots)

## Do not auto-commit

Sync copies files locally only. SVN commit and tagging are release actions — use the `wordpress-org-svn-release` skill when the user wants to publish.

## Version rule

Before any release, `vendorhub.php` `Version:` must match `readme.txt` `Stable tag:`.
